      "data": {
        "title": "Current Twilite State",
        "evidencePayload": "Twilite already has real declaration-based roots, public tutorial shelves, task fronts, explicit class bindings, bridge doctrine, contract graphs, editor/browser mode behavior, and live-served graph content. The important habit is to trace behavior back to authored graph truth first, then to runtime code when the graph is correct. Semantic zoom and remaining polish fronts still exist, but the substrate is already substantial enough for bounded real work.",
        "source": "repo and graph inspection",
        "timestamp": "current",
