      "data": {
        "title": "What a Twilite-capable agent should know",
        "outputPayload": "A Twilite-capable agent should know where doctrine lives, how declarations expose surfaces, how portals and consumers open those surfaces, how bridges grant authority, how class bindings shape authored nodes, and how to separate graph-content fixes from runtime fixes. It should also know how to move from orientation into a bounded task and leave a visible verification trail.",
        "status": "active",
        "confidence": "high",
        "qualityNote": "This graph is meant to function as the standing operating manual for Twilite-capable agents, not just a brief onboarding card.",
